s%20%24800%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20touted%20itself%20as%20being%20able%20to%20help%20with%20social%20and%20emotional%20learning.%20The%20robot%2C%20which%20launched%20early%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20eventually%20lost%20funding%20and%20shut%20down.%20Parents%20whose%20kids%20had%20become%20attached%20to%20their%20robot%20friends%20were%20distraught.%20The%20company%20figured%20out%20an%20open-source%20solution%20so%20owners%20could%20keep%20their%20robots%20going%20after%20its%20corporate%20owners%20had%20left%20them%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dafae87e-52ab-42ae-99fe-0e09da77a90a%5C%22%3EResearch%20on%20AI%20chatbots%20for%20kids%20is%20limited%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-openai-ai-dictionary-help-understand-nvidia-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELarge%20language%20models%2C%20or%20LLMs%2C%20like%20ChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20are%20still%20very%20new%2C%20and%20there%20hasn't%20been%20a%20huge%20body%20of%20scientific%20or%20academic%20research%20into%20how%20teens%20and%20kids%20use%20AI%20chatbots%20or%20might%20be%20affected%20by%20them.%20Other%20than%20limiting%20sexual%20or%20violent%20content%2C%20there%20isn't%20universal%20guidance%20on%20how%20to%20design%20a%20chatbot%20for%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDane%20Witbeck%20of%20Pinwheel%2C%20which%20makes%20kid-friendly%20phones%2C%20said%20squeezing%20AI%20chatbots%20into%20apps%20for%20kids%20and%20teens%20is%20a%20bad%20idea.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20give%20kids%20technology%20that's%20not%20designed%20for%20kids%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20designed%20for%20adults%20%E2%80%94%20we've%20already%20seen%20there%20are%20real%20harms%2C%20and%20the%20downsides%20can%20be%20severe.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20researcher%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cam.ac.uk%2Fresearch%2Fnews%2Fai-chatbots-have-shown-they-have-an-empathy-gap-that-children-are-likely-to-miss%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20University%20of%20Cambridge%20published%20a%20paper%20this%20past%20June%20urging%3C%2Fa%3E%20LLMs%20aimed%20at%20kids%20to%20be%20designed%20in%20a%20child-safe%20way%2C%20especially%20considering%20what%20it%20called%20the%20%26quot%3Bempathy%20gap%26quot%3B%20in%20chatbots%20that%20kids%20don't%20often%20pick%20up%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYing%20Xu%2C%20assistant%20professor%20of%20AI%20in%20learning%20and%20education%20at%20Harvard%20University%2C%20has%20been%20studying%20how%20AI%20can%20help%20elementary%20school-age%20kids%20with%20literacy%20and%20math.%20Xu%20sees%20good%20potential%20for%20educational%20settings.%20(She%20cited%20the%20Khan%20Academy%20Kids%20app%20as%20an%20example%20of%20AI%20being%20used%20well%20for%20kids.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EXu%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20although%20there%20is%20already%20research%20on%20how%20kids%20use%20things%20like%20Siri%20and%20Alexa%2C%20the%20more%20complex%20nature%20of%20the%20new%20LLMs%20hasn't%20fully%20been%20understood%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20studies%20that%20have%20started%20to%20explore%20the%20link%20between%20ChatGPT%2FLLMs%20and%20short-term%20outcomes%2C%20like%20learning%20a%20specific%20concept%20or%20skill%20with%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20over%20email.%20%26quot%3BBut%20there's%20less%20evidence%20on%20long-term%20emotional%20outcomes%2C%20which%20require%20more%20time%20to%20develop%20and%20observe.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJames%20Martin%2C%20CEO%20of%20Dante%2C%20an%20AI%20company%20that%20creates%20chatbots%20for%20various%20uses%2C%20including%20educational%20ones%20for%20kids%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20parents'%20concerns%20are%20justified.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOversharing%20isn't%20just%20possible%2C%20it's%20inevitable%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BKids%20tell%20AI%20things%20they%20wouldn't%20tell%20parents%2C%20teachers%2C%20friends.%20The%20AI%20doesn't%20judge.%20It%20doesn't%20guide.%20It%20just%20responds.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2237606833-e154-47d0-af79-1c5c6e54bdc0%5C%22%3EHow%20adults%20can%20think%20of%20AI%20for%20their%20kids%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20consider%20children%20still%20young%20enough%20to%20believe%20in%20Santa%20Claus%2C%20you%20can%20imagine%20how%20using%20chatbots%20that%20talk%20like%20humans%20can%20sometimes%20be%20confusing.%20It's%20hard%20enough%20for%20some%20adults%20who%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-world-network-chatbots-dating-romance-flirting-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eformed%20romantic%20attachments%20to%20AI%20chatbots%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20concern%20about%20how%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2025%2F02%2F24%2Fhealth%2Fai-therapists-chatbots.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20chatbots%20are%20being%20used%20for%20mental%20health%20support%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20LLMs%20can%20tend%20to%20reinforce%20what%20you're%20saying%20rather%20than%20challenge%20you%2C%20as%20a%20human%20therapist%20might.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETatiana%20Jordan%2C%20CMO%20of%20Bark%2C%20a%20company%20that%20makes%20parental%20control%20monitoring%20software%20and%20phones%20designed%20for%20kids%20and%20teens%2C%20said%20that%20right%20now%2C%20we're%20at%20a%20time%20when%20no%20one%20knows%20for%20sure%20how%20AI%20chatbots%20affect%20young%20people%20emotionally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20%3Cem%3Ejust%3C%2Fem%3E%20getting%20studies%20about%20what%20the%20past%2015%20years%20of%20screen%20time%20has%20done%20to%20kids%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%20all%20the%20industry%20watchers%20I%20spoke%20to%20agreed%20on%20one%20thing%3A%20AI%20chatbots%20are%20here%20to%20stay%2C%20and%20parents%20should%20think%20about%20how%20to%20safely%20teach%20their%20kids%20how%20to%20use%20them%20rather%20than%20avoid%20them%20completely%20and%20hope%20they'll%20go%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNone%20of%20us%20can%20stop%20what's%20coming%20with%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20Jordan%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20to%20educate%20our%20kids%20that%20it's%20a%20tool.%20It%20can%20be%20a%20positive%20tool%20or%20a%20harmful%20one.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparents-kids-ai-chatbots-apps-danger-benefits-study-how-to-2025-03%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1740914461000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67c20b45b8b41a9673f957de%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparents-kids-ai-chatbots-apps-danger-benefits-study-how-to-2025-03%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22AI%20chatbots%20are%20raising%20some%20concerns%20as%20they're%20appearing%20in%20more%20kid-friendly%20apps.%20There's%20limited%20research%20on%20their%20social%20and%20emotional%20impact.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22knotopoulos%40businessinsider.com%20(Katie%20Notopoulos)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparents-kids-ai-chatbots-apps-danger-benefits-study-how-to-2025-03%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20quit%20my%209-to-5%20in%20crypto%20and%20started%20an%20e-commerce%20business%20that%20made%20%241.3%20million%20in%20sales%20last%20year.%20I%20work%2024%2F7%20because%20I%20love%20it.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Yong-Soo%20Chung.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67c1de4cb1834fe31165ca09%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22810%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EYong-Soo%20Chung.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Yong-Soo%20Chung%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EYong-Soo%20Chung%20left%20his%20job%20as%20a%20software%20engineer%20at%20Ripple%20in%202015%20after%20the%20startup%20was%20fined.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20launched%20an%20e-commerce%20business%20and%20doesn't%20regret%20leaving%20his%209-to-5%20for%20a%20second.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EChung%2C%20whose%20business%20brought%20in%20over%20%241%20million%20in%20sales%20last%20year%2C%20said%20he%20loves%20entrepreneurship.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Yong-Soo%20Chung%2C%20a%2038-year-old%20entrepreneur.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%20Business%20Insider%20verified%20Chung's%20past%20employment%20and%20businesses.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202014%2C%20I%20worked%20a%209-to-5%20at%20what%20was%20then%20a%20crypto%20blockchain%20startup.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20joined%20them%20around%20March%202014%2C%20and%20it%20was%20an%20amazing%20experience.%20A%20year%20later%2C%20we%20were%20investigated%20by%20FinCEN%20about%20a%20platform%20we'd%20launched%20that%20allowed%20cross-border%20transactions%20on%20the%20blockchain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20May%202015%2C%20FinCEN%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fincen.gov%2Fnews%2Fnews-releases%2Ffincen-fines-ripple-labs-inc-first-civil-enforcement-action-against-virtual%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efined%3C%2Fa%3E%20Ripple%20%24700%2C000%20for%20operating%20as%20a%20money%20services%20business%20without%20registering%20and%20failing%20to%20implement%20an%20adequate%20anti-money%20laundering%20program.%20This%20basically%20put%20a%20pause%20on%20all%20of%20our%20development.%20It%20was%20really%20strange%20to%20go%20from%20rolling%20on%20all%20cylinders%20to%20suddenly%20being%20blocked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20day%2C%20I'd%20sit%20at%20my%20desk%20as%20a%20software%20engineer%2C%20knowing%20we%20couldn't%20do%20much.%20I%20was%20miserable%20and%20depressed.%20I%20eventually%20decided%20to%20quit%20and%20left%20my%209-to-5%20in%20September%202015.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20friends%20at%20the%20time%20called%20me%20crazy.%20Now%2C%20I%20call%20them%20crazy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2257247a12-ce8b-4b76-9b4c-d7598b7f6bee%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EStart%20your%20business%20around%20hobbies%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Ripple%20was%20fined%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20leave%2C%20but%20I%20needed%20a%20plan.%20I%20had%20around%20%2410%2C000%20saved%20to%20invest%20in%20a%20business%2C%20so%20I%20spent%20the%20summer%20coming%20up%20with%20an%20idea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20reviewed%20my%20credit%20card%20statements%20to%20see%20what%20I%20was%20spending%20money%20on%20and%20whether%20I%20could%20build%20a%20business%20out%20of%20my%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20got%20me%20into%20the%20rabbit%20hole%20of%20everyday%20carry%20gear%2C%20like%20wallets%2C%20knives%2C%20and%20pens.%20I'd%20spent%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20on%20these%20products%20and%20was%20obsessed%20with%20things%20that%20lasted%20a%20long%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20summer%2C%20I%20started%20building%20an%20Instagram%20audience%20of%20people%20who%20were%20into%20pocket%20items.%20Once%20I%20felt%20I%20had%20a%20solid%20audience%2C%20I%20left%20Ripple%20in%20September%202015%20and%20launched%20the%20Urban%20EDC%20shop%2C%20an%20e-commerce%20brand%2C%20in%20October%202015.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223c41b24b-afdc-400b-a663-6fa8af3e4c1b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBusiness%20ideas%20come%20from%20unexpected%20places%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20did%20weekly%20product%20drops%20releasing%20new%20products%20every%20Wednesday%20while%20continuing%20to%20build%20my%20email%20list%20and%20Instagram%20audience.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20gave%20me%20a%20great%20mechanism%20for%20feedback%3A%20every%20week%2C%20I%20would%20see%20what%20did%20well%20and%20what%20didn't.%20Then%2C%20I%20knew%20what%20kind%20of%20products%20I%20needed%20to%20sell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20everyday%20carry%20community%20is%20very%20tight-knit%2C%20with%20many%20people%20creating%20products%2C%20so%20we%20reached%20out%20to%20some%20for%20collaborations.%20We%20were%20initially%20profitable%20because%20we%20focused%20on%20sell%20low-cost%20items.%20However%2C%20the%20profits%20were%20difficult%20to%20live%20off%2C%20and%20we%20were%20had%20to%20be%20scrappy.%20I%20remember%20working%20for%20a%20month%20straight%20and%20not%20going%20out%20once.%20I%20was%20very%20focused%20on%20generating%20more%20cash%20flow%2C%20and%20we%20slowly%20built%20the%20business%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20launched%20our%20second%20business%20in%202017%20after%20getting%20a%20French%20bulldog.%20We%20made%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fspottedhumphrey%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInstagram%20account%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20dog%2C%20and%20it%20exploded.%20We%20now%20have%20122%2C000%20followers%20as%20well%20as%20a%20TikTok%20audience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFollowers%20were%20asking%20us%2C%20%26quot%3BWhere%20did%20you%20get%20that%20harness%3F%20Where%20did%20you%20get%20that%20leash%3F%26quot%3B%20My%20wife%20suggested%20creating%20a%20business%20similar%20to%20what%20I%20have%20with%20EDC%20gear%20but%20for%20Frenchie%20lovers%20and%20dog%20owners.%20My%20EDC%20business%20was%20growing%20very%20steadily%2C%20so%20why%20not%20copy%20the%20same%20model%20for%20a%20different%20audience%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20exactly%20what%20we%20did%3A%20my%20wife%20created%20Spotted%20by%20Humphrey%2C%20an%20online%20boutique%20for%20dog%20apparel%20and%20dog%20accessories.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226202%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Yong-Soo%20Chung%20(right)%2C%20his%20wife%20(left)%20and%20their%20French%20bulldog.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F676ad964e3e473ef263af427%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224135%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EYong-Soo%20Chung's%20wife%20created%20an%20online%20boutique%20for%20dog%20apparel%20and%20dog%20accessories%20after%20their%20French%20bulldog%20gained%20traction%20on%20social%20media.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Yong-Soo%20Chung%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20created%20two%20businesses%20based%20on%20our%20hobbies%20and%20interests.%20I%20don't%20feel%20like%20there's%20a%20work-life%20balance%20because%20I%20don't%20feel%20like%20I'm%20working.%20I%20work%20almost%20every%20moment%20I%20can%2C%20eight%20to%2010%20hours%20a%20day%2C%20including%20weekends%2C%20because%20I%20enjoy%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20initially%20ran%20the%20businesses%20ourselves.%20But%20as%20we%20grew%2C%20we%20were%20stuck%20at%20around%20%2480%2C000%20a%20month%20in%20topline%20revenue.%20I%20started%20to%20delegate%20customer%20support%20and%20grew%20our%20team%20to%20about%205%20to%207%20people%20in%20the%20US.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225d2fb03c-5884-4cb1-83fc-167d41f79eea%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECutting%20back%20on%20expenses%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20EDC%20company%20had%20sales%20of%20over%20%243%20million%20in%202022%2C%20but%20that%20was%20at%20the%20peak%20of%20post-pandemic%20e-commerce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20paying%20a%20lot%20on%20salaries%20for%20our%20employees%20and%20software%2C%20and%20our%20revenues%20were%20declining%2C%20so%20from%20mid-2023%20to%20early%202024%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20essentially%20cut%20everything%20%E2%80%94%20employees%20and%20software%20%E2%80%94%20and%20come%20back%20to%20just%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20hired%20a%20US-based%20contractor%20and%20outsourced%20a%20team%20of%20five%20in%20the%20Philippines.%20The%20business%20became%20profitable%20again%2C%20and%20we%20didn't%20need%20all%20these%20overhead%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20we're%20on%20good%20grounds%20and%20rebounding.%20The%20company%20is%20growing%20again.%20I%20don't%20feel%20like%20we're%20regressing.%20We%20made%20%241.3%20million%20in%20sales%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222701bce8-6886-46b6-b18c-a8f9b92c0c57%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou'll%20never%20feel%20ready%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20will%20never%20be%20100%25%20ready%20to%20start%20your%20own%20business.%20Most%20people%20stay%20in%20a%20job%20they%20don't%20enjoy%2C%20and%20are%20living%20in%20a%20mediocre%20middle%20ground%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0happy%20but%20not%20happy.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20an%20entrepreneur%20has%20probably%20stretched%20me%20physically%2C%20mentally%2C%20and%20emotionally.%20You%20can%20get%20into%20dark%20moments%2C%20and%20you%20don't%20have%20anyone%20to%20blame%20but%20yourself.%20It's%20all%20your%20responsibility.%20But%20it's%20rewarding%20getting%20yourself%20out%20of%20those%20times.%20In%20a%20strange%20way%2C%20you%20want%20your%20challenges%20to%20become%20bigger%20because%20it's%20a%20sign%20that%20you're%20growing%20as%20a%20business.%20Being%20an%20entrepreneur%20has%20taught%20me%20a%20lot%20about%20myself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20recommend%20just%20making%20a%20jump%20or%20even%20starting%20a%20side%20hustle.%20I've%20traded%20a%20career%20in%20blockchain%2C%20where%20I'd%20be%2013%20years%20in%20and%20making%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20by%20now%2C%20for%20entrepreneurship%2C%20and%20I%20have%20no%20regrets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20it's%20important%20to%20look%20at%20your%20life%20daily%20and%20question%20how%20you%20want%20to%20spend%20your%20time.%20You%20want%20to%20optimize%20for%20enjoyment.%20I%20enjoy%20the%20highs%20and%20lows%20of%20entrepreneurship.%20I%20can't%20imagine%20going%20back%20to%209-to-5%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-tech-job-e-commerce-business-no-regrets-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1740914221000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67c0638cb8b41a9673f925ee%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-tech-job-e-commerce-business-no-regrets-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Yong-Soo%20Chung%20quit%20his%209-to-5%20at%20crypto%20startup%20to%20build%20his%20own%20online%20business%2C%20which%20now%20makes%20over%20%241%20million%20a%20year.%20He%20says%20he%20has%20no%20regrets.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tspirlet%40insider.com%20(Thibault%20Spirlet)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-tech-job-e-commerce-business-no-regrets-2025-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Watch%3A%20Protesters%20target%20JD%20Vance%20in%20Vermont%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1740913300000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.files.bbci.co.uk%2Fws%2Fsimorgh-assets%2Fpublic%2Fnews%2Fimages%2Fmetadata%2Fposter-1024x576.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fvideos%2Fc2ljkny0j00o%233%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20vice-president%20and%20his%20family%20reportedly%20moved%20to%20an%20undisclosed%20location%20from%20their%20planned%20ski%20resort%20as%20a%20result.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fvideos%2Fc2ljkny0j00o%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22That%20humanities%20degree%20might%20come%20in%20handy%20if%20you%20want%20a%20job%20in%20AI%2C%20the%20editorial%20director%20at%20Google's%20NotebookLM%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224241%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Google%20Labs%20editorial%20director%20Steven%20Johnson%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67c0dc46b1834fe31165baf5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223371%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESteven%20Johnson%20told%20BI%20that%20we've%20entered%20an%20era%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Brevenge%20of%20the%20humanities.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ESteven%20Johnson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20editorial%20director%20of%20NotebookLM%20told%20BI%20that%20humanities%20skills%20are%20gaining%20value%20in%20AI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESteven%20Johnson%20says%20a%20new%20%26quot%3BAI%20wrangler%26quot%3B%20role%20requires%20knowledge%20of%20models%20and%20what%20they%20can%20do.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20said%20philosophical%20and%20psychological%20skills%20are%20increasingly%20important.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ETraditionally%2C%20a%20degree%20in%20the%20humanities%20wouldn't%20translate%20to%20a%20job%20in%20tech%20%E2%80%94%20but%20that%20might%20change%20in%20the%20age%20of%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20with%20Business%20Insider%2C%20Steven%20Johnson%2C%20who%20co-founded%20several%20startups%20and%20worked%20as%20an%20author%20before%20becoming%20editorial%20director%20of%20NotebookLM%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-google-labs-ar-vr-iris-blockchain-crypto-metaverse-web3-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%20Labs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20humanities%20might%20be%20making%20a%20comeback.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohnson%2C%20who%20is%20helping%20to%20build%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-notebooklm-ai-podcast-tool-customize-feature-update-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle's%20AI-powered%20note-taking%20%3C%2Fa%3Eand%20research%20tool%20NotebookLM%2C%20said%20in%20the%20age%20of%20large%20language%20models%2C%20there's%20a%20%26quot%3Brevenge%20of%20the%20humanities.%26quot%3B%20Not%20only%20is%20an%20English%20major%20valuable%2C%20but%20philosophical%20and%20psychological%20skills%20are%20also%20useful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20just%20a%20whole%20set%20of%20questions%20around%20AI%20that%20no%20one%20was%20thinking%20about%2C%20except%20for%20philosophers%2C%20until%20about%20two%20years%20ago%2C%26quot%3B%20Johnson%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20%26quot%3Bthose%20kinds%20of%20philosophical%20skills%20are%20really%20important.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohnson%20said%20fine-tuning%20a%20model's%20tone%20and%20conversational%20mode%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bhuge%20part%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20product.%20He%20pointed%20to%20Amanda%20Askell%2C%20a%20philosopher%20who%20works%20as%20an%20alignment%20fine-tuning%20researcher%20for%20Anthropic%2C%20as%20an%20example%20of%20someone%20who%20does%20%26quot%3Bcharacter%20training%26quot%3B%20for%20AI%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20June%20interview%20posted%20by%20Anthropic%20on%20YouTube%2C%20Askell%20said%20philosophy%20doesn't%20always%20line%20up%20with%20every%20aspect%20of%20her%20work%2C%20but%20building%20Claude's%20character%20feels%20%26quot%3Bphilosophically%20rich.%26quot%3B%20She%20said%20she%20has%20to%20work%20through%20complex%20questions%20like%20whether%20AI%20models%20should%20have%20moral%20considerations%20and%20what%20human%20principles%20they%20should%20be%20trained%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLots%20of%20people%20are%20like%2C%20'See%2C%20I%20told%20you%20the%20degree%20would%20be%20useful%2C'%26quot%3B%20Askell%20said%20in%20response%20to%20a%20question%20about%20whether%20it%20was%20strange%20to%20be%20a%20philosopher%20training%20an%20AI%20model.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20and%20Anthropic%20aren't%20the%20only%20companies%20recognizing%20the%20value%20of%20a%20humanities%20degree.%20One%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-companies-hiring-liberal-arts-humanities-grads-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20startup%20founder%3C%2Fa%3E%20told%20BI%20they%20seek%20out%20and%20said%20those%20with%20liberal%20arts%20backgrounds%20have%20a%20%26quot%3Bcreative%20and%20human-centric%20approach%26quot%3B%20and%20a%20strong%20understanding%20of%20how%20AI%20can%20be%20applied%20in%20their%20fields.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2270996b79-cc33-4020-b19b-b4b15b587b56%5C%22%3EThe%20role%20of%20the%20'AI%20wrangler'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20started%20at%20Google%20Labs%2C%20Johnson%20initially%20helped%20write%20prompts%20for%20AI%20models.%20As%20the%20AI%20boom%20took%20off%2C%20the%20role%20of%20prompt%20engineer%20similarly%20captured%C2%A0the%20attention%20of%20other%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fenglish-literature-major-mit-opencourseware-ai-data-science-job-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEnglish%20majors%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0interested%20in%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohnson%20said%20that%20prompting%20will%20change%2C%20especially%20as%20AI%20models%20improve%20at%20rewriting%20prompts%20%E2%80%94%20but%20a%20new%20role%2C%20which%20he%20referred%20to%20as%20the%20%26quot%3BAI%20wrangler%2C%26quot%3B%20has%20emerged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20maybe%20the%20next%20stage%20of%20the%20prompt%20engineer%2C%26quot%3B%20Johnson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohnson%20describes%20the%20AI%20wrangler%20role%20as%20not%20necessarily%20requiring%20coding%20expertise%20but%20involving%20deep%20knowledge%20of%20the%20latest%20models%20and%20their%20capabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20if%20someone%20wants%20to%20create%20a%2030-second%20animated%20video%20with%20AI%2C%20the%20AI%20wrangler%20would%20know%20the%20best%20tool%20for%20that%20task%20and%20how%20to%20use%20it%2C%20Johnson%20said.%20He%20said%20the%20role%20requires%20a%20%26quot%3Bcertain%20level%20of%20technical%20sophistication%26quot%3B%20but%20doesn't%20require%20knowing%20how%20to%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohnson%20said%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20skills%20to%20learn%20right%20now%20is%20fluency%20in%20the%20latest%20models%20and%20their%20functions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20just%20a%20general%20purpose%20skill%20that%20is%20actually%20going%20to%20be%20valuable%20in%20every%20single%20industry%2C%26quot%3B%20Johnson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e4b911a1-3d86-4567-8736-6fe3138b4151%5C%22%3ETechnical%20skills%20aren't%20going%20away%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20may%20be%20a%20growing%20need%20for%20humanities%20skills%20to%20help%20build%20how%20models%20interact%2C%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20that%20technical%20skills%20are%20no%20longer%20valuable%20or%20necessary.%20Those%20from%20a%20humanities%20background%20may%20need%20to%20skill%20up%20in%20technical%20areas%20to%20open%20up%20opportunities%20for%20themselves%20in%20the%20field.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-career-journey-ai-sales-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20Google%20AI%20sales%20leader%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20studied%20journalism%20and%20started%20his%20career%20in%20filmmaking%20eventually%20joined%20the%20tech%20giant%20in%20its%20media%2C%20entertainment%2C%20and%20gaming%20sectors%20for%20AI%20sales.%20However%2C%20he%20told%20BI%20he%20had%20to%20earn%20technical%20certifications%20and%20work%20his%20way%20up%20in%20engineering%20roles%20before%20taking%20on%20AI%20leadership%20roles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohnson%2C%20a%20published%20author%20of%2014%20books%2C%20came%20to%20Google%20with%20a%20strong%20understanding%20of%20technology%2C%20having%20sold%20startups%20and%20written%20extensively%20on%20the%20subject.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20going%20to%20try%20and%20make%20API%20calls%20to%20a%20bunch%20of%20these%20models%2C%20you%20probably%20need%20some%20more%20technical%20skills%2C%26quot%3B%20Johnson%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20%26quot%3B%20if%20someone%20wants%20to%20hire%20you%20to%20get%20the%20best%20outputs%20out%20of%20the%20best%20models%2C%20you%20don't%20really%20need%20a%20lot%20of%20technical%20skills%20to%20do%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnotebooklm-editorial-director-google-labs-said-humanities-skills-valuable-ai-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1740913021000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67c0dc7069253ccddf97d8db%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnotebooklm-editorial-director-google-labs-said-humanities-skills-valuable-ai-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20editorial%20director%20of%20NotebookLM%20a