wfh-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworkday%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20too%20long%20doctor's%20appointment%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-sick-leave-pto-mental-health-work-from-home-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elingering%20cold%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20a%20visit%20to%20the%20emergency%20veterinarian%2C%20canceling%20plans%20can%20be%20an%20understandable%20relief.%20Or%20as%20the%20comedian%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-famous-comedians-got-started-comics-stand-up-comedy%23john-mulaney-was-an-office-assistant-at-comedy-central-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJohn%20Mulaney%3C%2Fa%3E%20put%20it%20in%20his%202012%20stand-up%20special%3A%20%26quot%3BIn%20terms%20of%20like%20instant%20relief%2C%20canceling%20plans%20is%20like%20heroin.%20It%20is%20an%20amazing%20feeling.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hedonistic%20benefits%20of%20canceling%20plans%20have%20in%20recent%20years%20gained%20a%20more%20philosophical%20underpinning.%20As%20the%20new%20mantra%20goes%3A%20You%20don't%20owe%20anyone%20anything.%20The%20thinking%20is%20that%20self-care%20is%20key%20%E2%80%94%20your%20needs%20should%20come%20first%2C%20even%20if%20you've%20committed%20to%20plans.%20So%20go%20ahead%2C%20ignore%20that%20party%20invitation%2C%20ghost%20a%20friend's%20texts%20(or%20block%20their%20number%20completely)%2C%20or%20cancel%20that%20dinner%20reservation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20Americans%2C%20particularly%20young%20people%2C%20have%20taken%20this%20idea%20to%20heart.%20In%20a%20YouGov%20survey%20conducted%20in%20June%202022%2C%2036%25%20of%20respondents%20said%20they%20often%20agreed%20to%20plans%20far%20in%20advance%20but%20realized%20closer%20to%20the%20date%20that%20they%20didn't%20want%20to%20participate.%20Among%20respondents%2018%20to%2029%2C%2056%25%20said%20they%20very%20or%20somewhat%20often%20made%20plans%20and%20then%20realized%20they%20didn't%20want%20to%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20another%20adage%20tells%20us%2C%20everything%20is%20good%20in%20moderation.%20As%20it%20turns%20out%2C%20that%20applies%20to%20backing%20out%20of%20the%20plans%20we%20make%20with%20other%20people.%20William%20Chopik%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20psychology%20at%20Michigan%20State%20University%2C%20has%20studied%20why%20people%20feel%20relief%20when%20they%20cancel%20plans%20%E2%80%94%20and%20how%20to%20best%20do%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20like%2C%20'Well%2C%20why%20do%20they%20feel%20that%20way%3F'%20Because%2C%20in%20a%20way%2C%20you're%20kind%20of%20rejecting%20another%20person%2C%26quot%3B%20Chopik%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20know%2C%20you're%20telling%20another%20person%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20hang%20out%20with%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20this%20might%20seem%20like%20an%20easier%20way%20of%20living%2C%20it%20has%20more%20sinister%20effects%20on%20our%20relationships%20and%20economics.%20If%20we%20don't%20owe%20anyone%20anything%2C%20we%20may%20start%20to%20view%20service%20workers%20as%20input-output%20machines%20to%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frestaurant-workers-plan-to-quit-abuse-from-customers-managers-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Escreamed%20at%3C%2Fa%3E%20rather%20than%20as%20human%20beings.%20We%20can%20pull%20the%20plug%20on%20a%20friend's%20Friday-night%20plans%20via%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fsex-relationships%2Fghosting%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etext%20message%3C%2Fa%3E%20saying%20we%20vaguely%20don't%20feel%20up%20to%20it%20%E2%80%94%20we%20don't%20have%20to%20view%20or%20hear%20the%20friend's%20disappointment.%20On%20a%20sociopolitical%20level%2C%20we%20might%20throw%20support%20behind%20movements%20to%20benefit%20ourselves%20even%20if%20they%20prove%20harmful%20to%20other%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20leads%20to%20all%20sorts%20of%20effects%20for%20ourselves%2C%20from%20loneliness%20and%20isolation%20to%20also%20just%20a%20lack%20of%20deep%20meaning%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Richard%20Cowden%2C%20a%20research%20scientist%20who%20studies%20topics%20including%20forgiveness.%20Cowden%20said%20there's%20an%20idea%20called%20relational%20meaning%2C%20where%20your%20meaning%20in%20life%20is%20fundamentally%20rooted%20in%20relationships%20%E2%80%94%20with%20family%2C%20friends%2C%20and%20broader%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWithout%20fulfilling%20this%20fundamental%20need%2C%20we%20struggle%20in%20different%20ways%2C%26quot%3B%20Cowden%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20many%20good%20reasons%20to%20cancel%20plans%3A%20an%20illness%2C%20a%20family%20emergency%2C%20a%20work%20meeting%20gone%20awry.%20A%20society%20where%20people%20feel%20able%20to%20adjust%20plans%20for%20legitimate%20reasons%20is%20a%20step%20forward.%20But%20for%20every%20emergency-driven%20cancellation%2C%20there%20are%20dozens%20more%20nebulous%20ones%20%E2%80%94%20where%2C%20yes%2C%20you%20could%20go%2C%20but%20a%20little%20voice%20in%20your%20head%20is%20telling%20you%20not%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20these%20little%20decisions%20to%20cancel%20add%20up%20to%20a%20lot%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-boomers-loneliness-optimism-happiness-marriage-social-isolation-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ealone%20time%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%202010%2C%20Americans%20spent%20an%20average%20of%20about%205.6%20hours%20a%20day%20alone%3B%20by%202023%2C%20that%20had%20risen%20to%20nearly%20seven%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FFLhnL%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Average%20hours%20spent%20alone%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22431%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EChopik%20tells%20me%20there%20are%20two%20big%20forces%20undergirding%20some%20of%20our%20newfound%20flakiness.%20One%20is%20the%20proliferation%20of%20what%20he%20calls%20busy%20culture%2C%20a%20nasty%20offspring%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-zs-unhealthy-obsession-side-hustle-culture-2021-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehustle%20culture%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Modern%20conveniences%20make%20life%20easier%2C%20but%20constant%20connectivity%20pushes%20us%20to%20work%20more%2C%20not%20less.%20And%20when%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-work-life-full-time-job-other-generations-jealous-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejobs%20consume%20every%20corner%20of%20our%20lives%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20we%20start%20to%20view%20social%20outings%20as%20a%20special%20privilege%20or%20event%20rather%20than%20something%20we%20should%20weave%20into%20our%20daily%20routine.%20Busy%20culture%2C%20Chopik%20says%2C%20is%20this%20illusion%20that%20we%20simply%20don't%20have%20enough%20time%20for%20each%20other%2C%20or%20that%20that%20time%20is%20overlaid%20on%20the%20rest%20of%20our%20lives%20rather%20than%20an%20integral%20part%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20reason%20is%20grimmer%3A%20We're%20getting%20in%20our%20heads%20about%20whether%20we're%20even%20worth%20spending%20time%20with.%20After%20all%2C%20one%20byproduct%20of%20the%20pandemic%20was%20a%20pronounced%20increase%20in%20anxiety%20disorders%20and%20social%20anxiety.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20have%20started%20to%20doubt%20the%20fact%20that%20people%20want%20to%20hang%20out%20with%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Chopik%20said.%20Indeed%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.uchicago.edu%2Fpodcasts%2Fbig-brains%2Fwhy-talking-strangers-will-make-you-happier-nicholas-epley%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%20suggests%3C%2Fa%3E%20we%20underestimate%20how%20positive%20we%20feel%20when%20someone%20reaches%20out%20to%20us.%20We%20may%20think%20that%20if%20we%20strike%20up%20a%20conversation%20with%20a%20stranger%20on%20the%20subway%2C%20they%20won't%20want%20to%20chat%20or%20it'll%20make%20the%20commute%20worse.%20But%20the%20opposite%20is%20true.%20We%20like%20talking%20to%20each%20other%20%E2%80%94%20we%20just%20don't%20think%20people%20want%20to%20hear%20from%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20insecurity%20runs%20counter%20to%20what%20most%20people%20want.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20good%20test%20is%20to%20think%20about%20how%20you%20would%20react%20to%20it%20if%20a%20friend%20reached%20out%20or%20wanted%20to%20hang%20out%20with%20you%20%E2%80%94%20you%20would%20probably%20be%20positively%20disposed%20to%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Chopik%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20then%20if%20I%20asked%20you%2C%20hey%2C%20reach%20out%20to%20a%20friend%20and%20just%2C%20like%2C%20ask%20how%20their%20day%20was%2C%20you'd%20be%20like%2C%20I%20don't%20know%2C%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20bother%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENiki%20Meyari%2C%20a%2020-year-old%20college%20student%20in%20Arizona%2C%20chalks%20some%20of%20that%20up%20to%20residual%20social%20fallout%20from%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20get%20used%20to%20that%20loneliness%20and%20that%20isolation%20or%20maybe%20only%20interacting%20digitally%20in%20ways%20that%20fully%20can't%20be%20replicated%20in%20real%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20Meyari%2C%20who%20was%20a%20teen%20when%20the%20pandemic%20started%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20think%20that%20desensitized%20a%20lot%20of%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it%20may%20seem%20trivial%20to%20send%20that%20%26quot%3BI%20can't%20come%26quot%3B%20text%2C%20we%20lose%20more%20than%20just%20a%20canceled%20plan%20when%20we%20back%20out%20of%20a%20scheduled%20meetup.%20For%20one%20thing%2C%20there's%20a%20counterintuitive%20hierarchy%20of%20cancellations.%20While%20you%20might%20assume%20it's%20not%20as%20big%20of%20a%20deal%20if%20a%20close%20friend%20cancels%20%E2%80%94%20you'll%20probably%20see%20them%20again%20%E2%80%94%20Chopik%20has%20found%20that%20that's%20more%20likely%20to%20faze%20you%20than%20a%20casual%20acquaintance%20canceling.%20That's%20partly%20because%20we%20expect%20the%20people%20close%20to%20us%20to%20honor%20their%20commitments%20%E2%80%94%20they%20do%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20owe%20us%20something.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20have%20taken%20this%20concept%2C%20and%20they're%20applying%20it%20to%20everyone%20in%20every%20situation%2C%20and%20I%20just%20don't%20think%20that's%20productive%2C%26quot%3B%20Ashley%20Corbo%2C%20a%2027-year-old%20content%20creator%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChopik%20has%20found%20that%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20canceling%20plans%2C%20there%20are%20better%20and%20worse%20ways%20to%20go%20about%20it.%20For%20those%20getting%20canceled%20on%2C%20excuses%20such%20as%20dealing%20with%20health%20or%20family%20issues%20are%20more%20reasonable%20than%20not%20feeling%20like%20it%20or%20poor%20planning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPulling%20the%20rug%20out%20from%20under%20those%20closest%20to%20us%20and%20leaning%20on%20dubious%20health%20reasons%20is%20starting%20to%20affect%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdeath-casual-fringe-friendships-gen-z-sad-jobs-alone-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efriend%20groups%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Americans%20are%20increasingly%20less%20likely%20to%20have%20a%20best%20friend%20%E2%80%94%20perhaps%20we're%20filling%20our%20social%20circles%20with%20acquaintances%20we%20might%20not%20be%20upset%20with%20when%20they%20cancel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20idea%20that%20canceling%20plans%20is%20a%20form%20of%20self-care%20may%20be%20backfiring.%20Chopik%20said%20the%20people%20we're%20closest%20to%20are%20actually%20included%20in%20our%20sense%20of%20self.%20The%20time%20we%20spend%20with%20friends%20is%20precious%2C%20and%20it%20feels%20costly%20to%20lose%20out%20on%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20placed%20comfort%20and%20convenience%20on%20a%20pedestal%20that%20it%20does%20not%20need%20to%20be%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20Meyari%20said.%20%26quot%3BIn%20turn%2C%20actually%2C%20in%20the%20long%20run%2C%20it%20makes%20us%20more%20uncomfortable%2C%20because%20we%20don't%20really%20have%20others%20to%20be%20with.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEconomically%2C%20places%20for%20socializing%2C%20like%20restaurants%2C%20have%20instituted%20new%20measures%20to%20protect%20their%20bottom%20lines%20from%20our%20flaky%20tendencies.%20Look%20no%20further%20than%20the%20dominance%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fny.eater.com%2F2023%2F8%2F3%2F23817542%2Freservation-fees-deposits-resy-opentable-nyc%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erestaurant%20reservation%20fees%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20no-show%20charges.%20In%20a%20survey%20conducted%20by%20OpenTable%20in%202021%2C%2028%25%20of%20respondents%20in%20the%20US%20said%20they%20hadn't%20shown%20up%20for%20a%20reservation%20over%20the%20past%20year.%20In%202022%2C%20OpenTable%20launched%20its%20reservation-deposits%20feature%20designed%20to%20help%20restaurants%20avoid%20no-shows%2C%20citing%20their%20thin%20profit%20margins.%20The%20company%20told%20BI%20that%2C%20from%20January%202024%20to%20December%202024%2C%20they%20found%20the%20global%20volume%20of%20no-shows%20for%20restaurants%20using%20the%20deposit%20feature%20was%20about%2050%25%20lower%20than%20for%20those%20that%20don't%20require%20a%20deposit.%20A%20spokesperson%20for%20Resy%2C%20another%20popular%20restaurant%20booking%20app%2C%20said%20that%20in%20September%202024%2C%20nearly%20one-fifth%20of%20New%20York%20City%20restaurants%20on%20the%20platform%20charged%20at%20least%20one%20cancellation%20fee.%20Nationally%2C%20it%20said%2C%2012%25%20of%20restaurants%20charged%20a%20fee%20that%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20restaurants%20are%20small%20businesses%20%E2%80%94%20every%20table%20that%20sits%20empty%20can%20have%20a%20significant%20impact%2C%20especially%20when%20the%20average%20profit%20margin%20of%20restaurants%20is%20razor%20thin%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Resy%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20newer%20isolationist%20tendencies%20%E2%80%94%20or%20the%20rarity%20of%20social%20gatherings%20%E2%80%94%20might%20also%20be%20giving%20people%20a%20shorter%20fuse.%20In%20a%202022%20survey%20of%20workers%20in%20the%20restaurant%20industry%20by%20the%20advocacy%20organization%20One%20Fair%20Wage%2C%2046%25%20of%20women%20said%20they'd%20experienced%20increased%20harassment%20from%20customers%20or%20supervisors%20during%20the%20pandemic.%20Anecdotally%2C%20service%20workers%20have%20said%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-work-in-retail-customer-behavior-is-getting-worse-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecustomers%20generally%20treat%20them%20worse%20than%20they%20used%20to%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20noticed%20that%20customers%20were%20starting%20to%20act%20almost%20like%20they%20were%20taking%20stuff%20out%20on%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20Cristian%20Cardona%2C%20who%20left%20her%20job%20in%20fast%20food%20in%202021%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffood-service-workers-why-they-left-during-the-pandemic-2021-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreviously%20told%20BI%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BThey%20would%20get%20upset%2C%20angry.%20Sometimes%20they%20would%20get%20violent%2C%20yell%20stuff%20at%20us%2C%20and%20it%20made%20it%20a%20hostile%20environment%20for%20us%20a%20lot%20of%20times.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20an%20intellectual%20and%20transcendental%20level%2C%20as%20Cowden%20said%2C%20there's%20a%20line%20of%20thinking%20that%20we%20become%20more%20human%20the%20more%20we%20depend%20on%20others%20and%20spend%20time%20together.%20And%20when%20you're%20stuck%20thinking%20you%20don't%20owe%20others%20anything%2C%20you%20might%20not%20have%20someone%20to%20help%20reel%20you%20back%20into%20reality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20flakiness%20can%20be%20frustrating%2C%20the%20rising%20tide%20of%20cancellations%20is%20not%20inevitable.%20The%20event%20companies%20Evite%20and%20Eventbrite%20said%20that%20people%20on%20the%20platforms%20were%20increasingly%20showing%20an%20interest%20in%20attending%20health%20and%20fitness%20events%2C%20fandom%20festivities%20such%20as%20cosplay%20events%2C%20and%20alternative-music%20festivals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20seen%20a%20ton%20of%20traditional%20things%2C%20people%20reverting%20back%20to%20book%20club%2C%20game%20nights%2C%26quot%3B%20Olivia%20Pollock%2C%20a%20hosting%20and%20etiquette%20expert%20at%20Evite%2C%20told%20BI.%20They%20may%20find%2C%20in%20those%20cases%2C%20that%20they%20owe%20it%20to%20each%20other%20to%20read%20that%20book%20or%20show%20up%20to%20play%20that%20game.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20individuals%2C%20we%20might%20also%20need%20to%20lean%20into%20something%20that%20modern%20luxuries%20aim%20to%20alleviate%3A%20discomfort.%20Feeling%20a%20bit%20uncomfortable%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20that%20means%20showing%20up%20to%20a%20party%20we're%20not%20enthusiastic%20about%20or%20trekking%20to%20a%20friend's%20house%20%E2%80%94%20can%20pay%20off%20in%20the%20long%20run.%20On%20the%20other%20side%20may%20be%20a%20friend%20or%20a%20party%20full%20of%20new%20friends.%20While%20it%20might%20feel%20more%20comfortable%20to%20stay%20home%20or%20go%20into%20facilitated%20digital%20interactions%20where%20you%20can%20disappear%20in%20a%20moment's%20notice%2C%20it's%20worth%20having%20to%20suffer%20through%20some%20small%20talk%20or%20meeting%20a%20stranger.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeyari%20recalled%20a%20piece%20of%20advice%20she%20received%20on%20balancing%20discomfort%3A%20Are%20you%20uncomfortable%20with%20actually%20going%20to%20something%2C%20or%20with%20the%20transition%20of%20having%20to%20get%20up%20and%20go%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20a%20lot%20of%20people%2C%20those%20lines%20just%20get%20blurred%3B%20they%20think%20just%20because%20they%20don't%20want%20to%20transition%2